description.narrative: 1. Number of monitoring and study reports on GTP II indicators and SDGs. 2. Increase in number of meeting by DAG high level forum 3. Number of partners and GoE accessing reliable data from AMP platform 4. Number of Poverty Analysis and other strategic studies

comment.narrative: 1. NPC is newly established with a limited capacity to monitor GTP II. 2. DAG high level forum meets once in a year 3. AMP data is not refined, and upgrading is underway while aid effectiveness survey is conducted in 2013.

1. Prepare DPG phase VI project document incorporating feedback and comments provided on the final review of DAG phase V project document. 2. Organize a consultative meeting on Ethiopias 10-year development plan. 3. Hold effective dialogue with the Government of Ethiopia on selected themes listed below - Tigray humanitarian situation - Triple nexus - National Election of Ethiopia 4. Ensure smooth transition of AMP management from Development Gateway to MOF IT department in a phased approach.

1. An international consultant with the support of a team comprised of DAG member agencies drafted the DPG phase VI project document incorporating feedbacks from all stakeholders including MoF, PDC and DPG members. 2. PDC launched the 10-year development plan of Ethiopia. DPG discussed on achievements of GTP II and HGER and challenges with PDC. 3. DPG ExCom advocated for unimpeded humanitarian access to Tigray region to reach communities in need. In addition, discussions with EHRC on Human Rights issues, NDRMC on Humanitarian Requirement Plan and triple nexus with particular focus in Tigray region and regular briefing on the national election was held to improved information flows. 4. MoF provided online training to AMP focal points. MoF prepared a training video on generating AMP reports and shared with users. Moreover, online Java training was provided to MoF AMP team. Statistical bulletin on ODA flows to Ethiopia for EFY 2012 prepared.

1. support the implementation of GTP II and SDGs through the preparation of the 10 year perspective plan; capacitating the Planning and Development Commission (PDC); review the status on GTP II and SDG implementation; continuous monitoring of mega public projects and enhancing the capacity of PDC to produce quality data for equity based planning, monitoring and decision making. 2. Effective dialogue and engagement with the Government for effective implementation and monitoring of national as well as global development plans. Monthly DAG Heads of Agency as well as ExCom meetings; functional and effective sector and technical working groups and High Level Forum on selected theme for policy discussions. 3. Strengthens development effectiveness by ensuring Ethiopia’s participation in the Global Partnership on Effective Development Cooperation (GPEDC) monitoring surveys; facilitating policy discussion and evidence-based programming in resilience building and capacity building to deliver the reform. - Support the management, maintenance and upgrading of the Aid Management Platform (AMP) that tracks Official Development Assistance flows to Ethiopia. Support smooth transition of AMP management from Development Gate way to Ministry of Finance.

1. DAG project financed the monitoring of mega public projects to identify implementation challenges and provide adequate and reliable data for decision makers to expedite completion. 2. Consultation on the 10-year development plan has been held with different groups including political parties and people with disabilities to create national ownership and receive feedback to refine the draft plan. 3. DAG held effective dialogue with GoE and within its structure to support the implementation of GTP II. HLF was held on COVID-19 response to map support from development partners. Policy discussion was held on Lowland Resilience Building Study to identify challenges and recommend way forward. 4. AMP training was conducted to new and existing AMP focal points to improve the quality of AMP data. The project financed the publication and dissemination of annual ODA statistical bulletin and donor profile.

Target 2019 1. Produce one Annual GTP II Progress Report; conduct nine regional and two city-administrative GTP II APR Consultation Workshop and one federal GTP II APR consultation with Development Partners. Conduct one High level economic forum on GTP II Progress 2.Conduct two HLF and eleven DAG ExCom and HoA meetings; Follow up implementation of DAG ExCom and HoA meetings action points. 3. Enhance technical capacity of AMP user focal points; Complete AAAA implementation roadmap with M&E framework; Organize Awareness creation workshop on development cooperation effectiveness and provide technical support to MoF top management;

1. PDC carried out a series of trainings for its staff on Results Based Management Monitoring and Evaluation, gender mainstreaming, economic modeling and e-service to build their capacity to effectively deliver their targets. - GTP II Annual Progress Review meeting were held in all regions and city administrations to assess implementation progress, identify challenges, deliberate and agree on way forward. - Performance assessment of various public projects was conducted throughout the country and the 10 year perspective plan of Ethiopia was drafted to identify national priorities in the coming 10 years. 2. DAG conducted effective dialogue with the Government on resilience building in Ethiopian lowlands; humanitarian situation of the country; 2020 national election, macro-economic performance; domestic resource mobilization and private public partnerships (PPP) with relation to Addis Ababa Action Agenda roadmap; regional integration & trade; the 10-year perspective plan and home grown economic reforms. In addition, the High-Level Forum, the monthly DAG Heads of Agency and Executive Committee meetings helped to improve collaborations among DAG members and with the Government. Furthermore, technical and Sector working group meets regularly to engage on sectoral issues and solutions in order to guide policy recommendations. 3. DAG pooled fund supporting the third round GPEDC monitoring survey; financed the publication of Official Development Assistance (ODA) Statistical Bulletin and Addis Ababa Action Agenda.
